at I still eat &#8212; poultry and fish &#8211;, which I think has robbed me of some essential nutrients. So I, too, am searching again for the meat balance.</p><div style="clear:both"></div><div class="reply"> <a class='comment-reply-link' href='/food/problem-eating-meat/?replytocom=14424#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-14424", "14424", "respond", "4412")'>Reply</a></div><div class="fix"></div></div><div class="fix"></div></div><ul class='children'><li class="comment byuser comment-author-Ayngelina bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-14483"> <a name="comment-14483"></a><div class="comment-container"><div class="comment-head"><div class="avatar"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/4becf0b7984bb629afd7809fc46987a0?s=37&amp;d=blank&amp;r=G' class='photo avatar avatar-37 photo' height='37' width='37' /></div> <span class="name"><span style="">Ayngelina</span></span> <span class="date">on the July 18, 2011 remarked</span> <span class="edit"></span> <span class="perma"><a href="http://www.baconismagic.ca/food/problem-eating-meat/#comment-14483" title="Direct link to this comment">#</a></span><div class="fix"></div></div><div class="comment-entry"  id="comment-14483"><div style="padding:10px 8px 3px 10px; background-color: #FFFFE0;"><p>You know after reading Eating Animals, the animal I struggle most with is chicken, I don&#8217;t know but I feel sick every time I think of eating it.</p></div><div style="clear:both"></div><div class="reply"> <a class='comment-reply-link' href='/food/problem-eating-meat/?replytocom=14483#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-14483", "14483", "respond", "4412")'>Reply</a></div><div class="fix"></div></div><div class="fix"></div></div></li></ul></li><li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-14427"> <a name="comment-14427"></a><div class="comment-container"><div class="comment-head"><div class="avatar"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/3aaa43bb43ea370d6c890